{
  "name": "OneFlare CF-AI-PromptInjection - LLM Abuse Response (Pyxis /api/v1/chat)",
  "description": "Alert-triggered AI-abuse response for the CF-AI-PromptInjection detection (rule 2519093028014740613): LLM prompt-injection / jailbreak probing of the Pyxis /api/v1/chat endpoint. Extracts the offending src_ip, runs two enrichment arms - (a) an S1 PowerQuery counting the same IP's chat POSTs over 24h (sustained campaign vs single probe) and (b) VirusTotal reputation of the src_ip - then branches on a verdict gate. Confirmed (VT-malicious OR sustained) -> hard-block the src_ip at Cloudflare on the AI endpoint + a zone IP Access block + S1 IOC + raise to TRUE_POSITIVE/HIGH. Unconfirmed single probe -> Cloudflare managed-challenge on the chat route + SUSPICIOUS/MEDIUM (pending confirmation). Both branches add an S1 note carrying the MITRE ATLAS technique (AML.T0054 LLM Prompt Injection / AML.T0057 LLM Data Leakage) and notify the AI-safety/SOC channel. run_automatically=false: analyst approves from the Singularity Response console. Network/identity-level response only - content-level input filtering at the app is complementary.",
